news.title: Axis Bank, Shriram Housing Finance announce partnership for co-lending
news.para: ​Through this partnership, both the lenders will offer secured MSME (Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises) loans and home loans to the middle and low-income segment borrowers based in rural and semi-urban regions, a joint statement said.

news.title: Rose Valley: ED attaches assets worth Rs 159 crore in money laundering case
news.para: ​A provisional order for attachment of assets has been issued under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) and as many as 139 immovable properties consisting land, flats, commercial and office space, shops etc. registered in the name of various companies of Rose Valley Group and its directors in Tripura, West Bengal, Andaman and Nicobar Islands, have been frozen, the agency said in a statement.

news.title: Revised estimate for Kochi metro phase II gets cabinet nod
news.para: The delay in land acquisition and commencement of the works have already caused the escalation of the entire project cost. The cabinet’s decision to grant approval for the revised estimate is expected to speed up the works on the second phase of the Metro line.

news.title: Nuveen invests $30 million in Aviom India Housing Finance
news.para: The primary investment size is $20 million with the balance is through secondary deals, an industry source familiar with the matter said.

news.title: Residential searches increase 14.2%, listings grew 1.9% in Jan-Mar 2023: Report
news.para: Magicbricks.com is owned by Magicbricks Realty Services, which is a subsidiary of Times Internet.

news.title: Plea against new buildings till water woes resolved in Pune
news.para: In addition to this the members of the Baner-Balewadi-Pashan Residents Association (BBPRA) raised issues like that of clearing unnecessary overhead cables, cleaning nullahs and storm-water drains before monsoons, among other things.

news.title: Fail to see how withholding OC to free sale unit, subserves public purpose: Bombay HC to MHADA
news.para: Kalra and 14 other free-sale flat buyers at Ekta Tripolis, a free-sale building in the 47-acre 672-tenant Patra Chawl redevelopment project on MHADA land, had petitioned the HC this year. Through senior counsel Zal Andhyarujia they sought the issuance of the OC.

news.title: Gurugram: FIR likely against Malibu Estate for illegal construction
news.para: District town planner (enforcement) Manish Yadav, in his letter to the police chief, sought registration of an FIR and action against the builder and any associates who were part of the illegal act.

news.title: Clear dues or face recovery certificates from April: Greater Noida authority
news.para: So far, 10 developers have applied to clear dues under the GNIDA’s reschedulement policy and made a part pay-ment, while five others have cleared their dues. There are a total 197 projects in the township.

news.title: Mukul Rohatgi's wife buys Golf Links bungalow for Rs 160 crore
news.para: Last year, former Solicitor General of India Gopal Subramanium bought a sprawling 866-square-yard bungalow at Lutyens' Delhi's Sunder Nagar locality for Rs 85 crore.

news.title: JP Taparia family buys triplex apartment in South Mumbai's Malabar Hill for Rs 369 crore
news.para: The apartment on the 26th, 27th and 28th floor of the super-luxury residential tower Lodha Malabar is located on the plush Walkeshwar Road, opposite the governor’s estate, touching both the Arabian Sea and the Hanging Gardens.

news.title: Vatika, its directors booked for fraud after Noida court order
news.para: A city-based builder and its directors have been booked for cheating, forgery and criminal conspiracy.

news.title: Mahindra World City Developers transfers 9.24 acres land to Alliance Budget Housing
news.para: Mahindra World City Developers has transferred land admeasuring 9.24 acres on perpetual lease within the Mahindra World City, Chennai to Alliance Budget Housing

news.title: Godrej Properties increases its stake in Wonder City Buildcon and Godrej Home Constructions
news.para: Pursuant to the said acquisition, Wonder City Buildcon and Godrej Home Constructions have become subsidiaries of Godrej Properties with effect from March 29, 2023.

news.title: TVS Emerald and HDFC Capital create Rs 1,000 crore platform for plotted development projects
news.para: Sriram Iyer, President & CEO of TVS Emerald said, "This is a strategic tie-up to grow our plotted development portfolio in the South markets."
